<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
          xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
          xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"
          xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
          version="5.0-subset Scilab"
          xml:id="XcosMenuPaste">
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>Paste</refname>
    <refpurpose>Menu: Paste the content of the Scicos Clipboard in the current diagram.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      The Scicos objects that had been previously put in the Scicos
      Clipboard by the <link linkend="XcosMenuCopy">Copy</link>
      or<link linkend="XcosMenuCut">Cut</link> menu can be pasted one
      or several time into any active Scicos edition window.
    </para>
    <para>
      To paste, the user, may first select (left click) the location
      of the bottom left corner of the area to be pasted and then
      activate the <literal>Paste</literal> menu. The pasted objects
      will be drawn et marked selected, so it is possible to move them
      if necessary.
    </para>
    <para>
      If the Cliboard contains a single block it is also possible to
      paste it over an already selected block. In this case the pasted
      block replaces the selected one.
     </para>
  
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>See Also</title>
    <simplelist type="inline">
      <member> <link linkend="XcosMenuCopy">Copy</link> </member>
      <member> <link linkend="XcosMenuDuplicate">Duplicate</link> </member>
     </simplelist>
   </refsection>
</refentry>
